# A List of Code That We Can't Get To Work

PODS Framework is an awesome software and we can see the potential of using it to maintain our site but we are amateurs learning as we go. If anyone out there knows the answer to any of our postings please help us. 

**1. This is the code that we are working on for our images:**
`  <P><img src="<?php echo $speaker_photo = wp_get_attachment_image_src( current( (array) $this->get_field( 'speaker_photo.ID' ) ), 'thumbnail' ); ?>" width="230" height="353" border="0" /></P>`

We need the image to display in a specific area in a specific size. We are using code and magic tags. But we can't get it to work. We imputed this code in our Pods Template.

***
2. **We are trying to get this Pods helper to work.** It is suppose to allow the user to make a selection and then display the selection in the output. But it only displays the number not the actual text. The text is what we need to be displayed. **The code is below:**

`<?php
$picktype = "checkbox"; // multiple selection, set to "radio" if you want radio buttons, checkbox for a checkbox list
$yourvalues_arr = array( // Input your own values for inclusion in a checkbox or radiobutton list
		0 => "Just Starting 0-9 Events", 
		1 => "Some Experience 10-25 Events", 
                2 => "Experienced 26+ Events", 
                3 => "Full Time- Over 30 Events per Year" 
            	);
// DO NOT EDIT BEYOND THIS POINT ( or you should know what you're doing ) - tomhermans.com

$css_classes = str_replace(array(' ' . $coltype . ' ', ' pods_coltype_' . $coltype . ' '), array(' pick ', ' pods_coltype_pick '), $css_classes);
?>
<div class="<?php echo esc_attr($css_classes); ?>" id="<?php echo esc_attr($css_id); ?>">
<?php
if(!empty($yourvalues_arr)) {
    $value_arr = explode(",", $value); // retrieve set value and explode to array of set values
    foreach($yourvalues_arr as $key => $val) {
        $selected = '';
        $active = '';
        if (in_array($key, $value_arr)) {
            $selected = ' CHECKED';
            $active = ' active';
        }
        $val = array('id' => $key, 'name' => $val);
?>
        <input type="<?php echo $picktype; ?>" id="checkbox_radio_<?php echo $name . '_' . $val['id']; ?>" name="<?php echo $name . ( 'checkbox' == $picktype ? '[]' : '' ); ?>" class="checkbox-radio-option<?php echo $active; ?>" value="<?php echo $val['id']; ?>" data-value="<?php echo $val['id']; ?>" <?php echo $selected; ?> />
        <label for="checkbox_radio_<?php echo $name . '_' . $val['id']; ?>"><?php echo $val['name']; ?></label><br />
<?php
	}
}
?>
</div>
<script type="text/javascript">
jQuery('#<?php echo $css_id; ?> input.checkbox-radio-option').on('change', function(){
    jQuery('#<?php echo $css_id; ?> input.checkbox-radio-option').removeClass('active');
    jQuery('#<?php echo $css_id; ?> input.checkbox-radio-option:checked').addClass('active');
});
</script>`
